<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:my="http://example.com/my" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_fadyn_2" n="2" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fadyn</orth><form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp"><orth>fast</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fadun</orth><form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp"><orth>fast</orth></form></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>покрываться сыпью</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>break out in a rash</q></cit></sense><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fadynæg</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fadængæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>корь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>measles</q></cit></sense><sense xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang xml:lang="ru"/><lang xml:lang="en"/></usg><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>распускаться (о цветке)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>blossom out</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_fadyn_2." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>jæ bwar rafasta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>его тело покрылось сыпью</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>his body got covered with a rash</q></cit></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>jæ bwar rafasta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>его тело покрылось сыпью</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>his body got covered with a rash</q></cit></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Происхождение не ясно. Если допустить, что в основе лежит понятие „красноты“ (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼitela</w><gloss><q>корь</q></gloss></mentioned> при <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼiteli</w><gloss><q>красный</q></gloss></mentioned>), то можно сблизить с <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pāṭala-</w><gloss><q>бледнокрасный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>paṭala-</w><gloss><q>нанесенное краской пятно на теле</q></gloss></mentioned>, .</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The origin is not clear. If one assumes that there is the concept of ‘redness’ in the stem (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼitela</w><gloss><q>measles</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼiteli</w><gloss><q>red</q></gloss></mentioned>), then it is possible to relate this word to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pāṭala-</w><gloss><q>light red</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>paṭala-</w><gloss><q>paint stain on a body</q></gloss></mentioned>, .</etym></entry>